ex products to key customers and partners mr vegesna currently serves as the chairman and managing director of sify technologies limited a publicly traded ict services company based in india after having purchased a majority stake in  realizing the emerging potential for enterprise it business both within and outside india mr vegesna set about aligning the company’s focus towards the same less than half a decade later sify is now recognized as a leader in the fast growing segments of ict services managed it services connectivity voice and cloud services in recognition of his entrepreneurial achievements raju was honored at the india splendor award event at ucla in  raju has proven to be a gifted entrepreneur having founded multiple highlysuccessful startup companies in  prior to his current involvement with serverengines and sify raju founded serverworks corporation and as chairman and ceo led serverworks to become the world leader in computer chipsets commanding a  market share in the x server chipset market kamal nath chief executive officer kamal nath joined sify to drive sify  the vision to make sify technologies a services and solutions leader he moves here after a stellar innings with it major hcl tech in his  years long tenure at hcl tech he has led various transformational engagements with large enterprises incubated business lines created innovative business models and opened up new and high growth verticals for hcl tech kamal was a founder member of hcl comnet the infrastructure services division of hcl tech and has been a key member of hcl tech’s growth story over the years his entrepreneurial style of functioning along with strategic vision innovation and leadership skills has seen him play several roles across different business units of hcl in a career spanning  years he has accumulated indepth knowledge of systems integration services it infrastructure management services technology integration services  strategic outsourcing his experience and engagement with customers of various verticals encompassing bfsi public services energy  utilities large business conglomerates manufacturing retail and others will be a key asset at sify kamal holds a degree in electronics and communications from bit sindri mp vijay kumar  chief financial officer vijay kumar a rank holder in chartered accountancy is a cost accountant and company secretary he joined sify in  as the cfo and has been a key member of sify’s transformation into a leading enterprise it infra and services player director on the board of sify software limited sify technologies singapore pte limited national internet exchange of india nixi and thejo engineering limitedthe first company to be listed in sme platform “emerge” of national stock exchange nse he was earlier on the board of mfg sify securities limited he was a partner for over  years with yoganandh  ram an established firm of chartered accountants chennai and registered with pcaob us prior to joining yoganandh  ram he was employed with sundaram finance services ltd sfsl chennai the investment banking arm of sundaram finance limited a topnotch nbfc that provides a wide range of financial services his responsibilities during his  year stint included head  investment banking head  finance accounts and company secretary he was assistant general manager ib  secretary when the entrepreneurship bug bit and he decided to move to yoganandh  ram he is a member of the accounting standards board of icai accounting standards board of cii task force on accounting for rate regulated entities editorial board of sirc of icai corporate laws committee of icai and also member of several study groups of icai on accounting standards audit assurance standards and company law he is a prominent speaker on the professional circuit in india the middle east and south east asia on international financial reporting standards ifrs indian accounting standards management audit corporate laws and capital market a well referenced resource person on accountancy corporate laws and capital market he is associated with the institute of chartered accountants of india the institute of company secretaries of india and bharatidasan institute of management bim also a successful author he has over  popular titles on accounting accounting standards audit standards and company law that have since enjoyed continious reprints a member of institute of internal auditors iia florida usa he is presently the governor and vice president on the board of governors chennai chapter of iia and was chairman of heads of finance forum for fy  and  cii tamil nadu this year he joins the southern regional council as a special invitee mandated with providing thought leadership and strategic direction for the year  he is active in corporate relations serving rotary in various capacities as a rotary paul harris fellow david nishball  chief strategy officer david nishball is one of the leading experts in building and managing enterprise telecom operations in the asia pacific region having led the enterprise segment for a number of global operators joint venture companies and emerging market operators he brings over twenty eight years of experience spanning various roles and functions in the telecommunications industry including  years in the asia pacific region most recently david was president of airtel enterprise services from  enterprise services is a strategic business unit of bharti airtel ltd indias leading telecom service provider prior to joining bharti airtel david was a senior vice president asia pacific for orange business services formerly equant based in singapore he managed oranges business operations in asean japan korea greater china india and australasia from  david held a number of strategic positions with att and its related companies  where he played a key role in supporting and managing several global ventures david was head of business sales and managed services for att asia pacific he also served as regional head of concert asia pacific a joint venture between bt and att where he led the global accounts sales carrier services and distribution organizations david was a founding officer of worldpartners company a global telecommunications services venture between att kdd japan singapore telecom and unisource serving as the vice president marketing david holds a master of business administration honors with focus on finance and operations research from the university of california at berkeley haas school of business and is also a bachelor of arts graduate in economics with engineering emphasis from the university pranesh babu k chief technology officer pranesh took over as chief technology officer in june  he joined sify technologies in oct  and has worked in various capacities in the technology division prior to this he was senior vice president – network and service engineering responsible for strategizing the core network and access network and for developing services he has been a key contributor to the sify’s network expansion and in developing services for both the enterprise and consumer divisions pranesh has over  years of experience in itites telecom industry and has handled diverse responsibilities which include projects service delivery  engineering he started his career with hcl ltd moving on to work with hutchison max telecom as chief network engineer and finally reliance telecom ltd as project manager before joining sify technologies in  pranesh holds an engineering degree from university of mysore in electronics and communications natesh mani  president – sales and marketing  cr rao  chief operating officer cr rao was elevated in april  as chief operating officer he had joined us on nd march  as vice president  strategy and was responsible for the administrative and hr functions in sify he has over  years of aviation industry experience and brings with him rich expertise in strategic planning operational management and organizational development initiatives he has extensively worked on business development and implementation of strategies and processes that drive enhanced business results and improve organisational capabilities he practiced law from  this was followed by assignments with delta tubes pvt ltd and an impressive stint with bobba aviation services – gsa lufthansa cargo where he held various senior positions cr rao holds graduate degrees in law and commerce from andhra university and postgraduate degree in business administration from osmania university news  analysis featured company the central europe russia and turkey fund inc new york ny us related links awards investor relations about us you may also be interested in groupe diffusion plus sa normanville hn fr groupe diffusion plus sa provides direct communications management and remote sales logistics services for businesses the companys two domains are shaw communications inc calgary ab ca shaw communications inc provides its customers with highquality entertainment information and communications services utilizing a variety of distribution technologies it blackrock municipal income quality trust wilmington de us × contact investor relations sify technologies ltd investor relations tidel park  rajiv gandhi salai nd floor taramani chennai  tn  india phone sic code  close × request investor kit select your country afghanistan aland islands albania algeria american samoa andorra angola anguilla antigua and barbuda argentina armenia aruba australia austria azerbaijan bahamas bahrain bangladesh barbados belarus belgium belize benin bermuda bhutan bolivia bonaire st eust saba bosnia and herzegovina botswana bouvet island brazil brit indian ocean terr british virgin islands brunei bulgaria burkina faso burundi cambodia cameroon canada cape verde cayman islands central african republic chad chile china christmas island cocos keeling islands colombia comoros congo dem rep of the congo rep of cook islands costa rica croatia cuba curacao cyprus czech republic denm